claim.claim-text:
Device for collection and treatment of biological samples characterized by comprising:
- a receptacle (8) with a conical or round-shaped end (10), at the center of which there is a conical or rounded-shape protuberance (11) and one or more holes (12);
- a cover (2), which comprises a pierceable area (3);
- a collector recipient (14) that contacts with one end of the receptacle (8).

Process for collection, storage and/or treatment of a biological sample, characterized by comprising the following steps:
a) Contacting the end of the collection arrangement (1) of the device described in any of the claims 1 to 4, with the anogenital, oropharyngeal or respiratory areas of origin of the biological sample to be collected;
b) Piercing of the cover (2) of the device and introduction of a washing solution into the receptacle (8);
c) Centrifuging the device;
d) Recovery of the biological sample at the bottom of the collector recipient.
